  "prompt": "How do I find the URL of a picture?",
  "response": "To find the URL of a picture, you can:\n\n1. On a web browser:\n- Right-click on the image\n- Select \"Copy image address\" or \"Copy image link\"\n- The URL will be copied to your clipboard\n\n2. On mobile:\n- Press and hold on the image\n- Select \"Copy image link\" or \"Copy image address\"\n\n3. Inspect method:\n- Right-click the image\n- Select \"Inspect\" or \"Inspect Element\"\n- Look for the <img> tag\n- The \"src\" attribute will contain the image URL\n\n4. Browser address bar:\n- Click on the image to open it full size\n- The URL in the address bar will be the image URL\n\n5. Social media:\n- On platforms like Facebook or Instagram, right-click the image\n- Choose \"Copy image address\"\n\n6. Google Images:\n- Right-click the image\n- Select \"Copy image address\"\n\nThe method may vary slightly depending on your device and browser, but these are the most common ways to find an image URL.",
